webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) View of Schedevi Castle, written out Skedevid. There is some uncertainty about the building’s time of access. Still, it is prevalent that the design began in 1781 and that the castle was completed a bit into the decade. Byggherre was the National Council and Count Melcher Falkenberg to Brokind and to architect he engaged Carl Fredril Adelcrantz. At the time of the picture, a nursing and working home had recently been set up in the castle for insane men - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000641. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419931. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
